      <constitutionalAuthorityStatementText>&lt;pre&gt;[Congressional Record Volume 169, Number 157 (Wednesday, September 27, 2023)][House]From the Congressional Record Online through the Government Publishing Office [&lt;a href="https://www.gpo.gov"&gt;www.gpo.gov&lt;/a&gt;]By Mr. MOOLENAAR:H.R. 5742.Congress has the power to enact this legislation pursuantto the following:Article 1, Section 8, clause 3: The Congress shall havePower. . .To regulate Commerce with foreign Nations, andamong the several States, and with the Indian Tribes;The single subject of this legislation is:This legislation would clarify that an employee under theFair Labor Standards Act does not include an individual whoperforms activities required as part of a vocational schoolcurriculum or training.[Page H4714]&lt;/pre&gt;</constitutionalAuthorityStatementText>
